events.name: Inaugural Meetup
events.description:
Welcome to GDG Mobile, Alabama! We are having our first meetup on April 23 at 5pm at the Fairhope Brewing Company. This will be a great time to meet some other local developers and discuss what talks, demos, and workshops you might be interested in!

Presentation topic: Overview of GDG and Google Cloud Platform

events.name: Firebase - Extend Your Website or App With Cloud Functions for Firebase
events.description:
With Firebase's Realtime Database and Cloud Functions you can add back-end functionality to your website or app without having to write any server-side code! In this session Ben Simmons, lead engineer of Sworkit (https://sworkit.com/) will show you how to get started with Firebase Cloud Functions and Firebase Realtime Database.

We will be meeting at The Exchange 202 in downtown Mobile on May 16th at 6pm. Along with learning how to get started with Firebase, this will also be a good opportunity to meet other local developers, share what projects you are working on, and to check out the awesome coworking space at The Exchange. As an added bonus, GDG Members will be able to access The Exchange FOR FREE on the day of the meetup!

events.name: August Meet & Greet
events.description: Our monthly meet & greet meetings will be an informal time to network with other devs from the area and also for us to gauge interest in the topics, programs, and speakers that GDG members would like to see in upcoming meetups.

events.name: Cloud Study Jam - Kubernetes
events.description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud and Kubernetes, but don't know where to begin? Join us at 6 pm on January 28th for our Cloud Study Jam at the Fairhope Brewing Company!

Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with Kubernetes and the Google Container Engine.

Then after our live session, you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to compete any labs you want!

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Donâ€™t forget your charger.

The event will be from 6-9pm at the Fairhope Brewing Company in Fairhope, Alabama.

events.name: Coffee & Code - Flutter
events.description:
---
UPDATE: We will be working on this Flutter codelab - https://codelabs.developers.google.com/codelabs/first-flutter-app-pt1/#0

Be sure to bring a laptop that has either Android Studio or XCode installed or a phone and USB cable to run your apps on.
---

Come grab some coffee with other developers from the area and work on a code lab together!

This month we will be looking at Flutter. Flutter is Google's mobile SDK for crafting high-quality native interfaces on iOS and Android in record time. Flutter works with existing code, is used by developers and organizations around the world, and is free and open source.

Come grab some coffee with other developers from the area and work on a code lab together!

This month we will be looking at Firebase. Firebase is not just a database service, it is an amazing platform that allows you to build full web and mobile apps without writing any server side code!
